        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 1:04PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 104 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hampton, or near Elizabethton, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hampton, Trade, Hunter, Roane Mountain State Park, Doeville, Neva,
Hampton Creek Cove State Park, Elk Mills, and Roan Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
